input_str: I’ve been told many things about Fuji, the mountain plastered over tons of Japanese paraphernalia, and the image synonymous with Japan. Apparently, you can see the curvature of the earth from the top, and on a bright day see to the very ends of the country. This being my first such expedition, I don’t know what to expect. “I want to see the rocks,” one of my climbing mates said to me earlier on the bus. She is Ana,
